 *1465891550* Participated in Unexplored IoT Development Camp #1
 Since the Unexplored Development Camp #0 held last year by the Unexplored Foundation was well received, we held a camp focusing on the IoT theme with the help of Mr. Masashi Ueda of the IoT Study Group.
 
 This time, while listening to Mr. Ueda's lecture, I connected a sensor and an LCD to the I2C bus and wrote data read from the sensor to the LCD. Thanks to this, I was able to deepen my understanding of I2C, which I did not understand very well before. So I put it all together in a slide presentation so that I can easily review it half a year later.
 
