 Sakura Internet, a corporate member of MISHOP, provided the alpha version of "Sakura IoT" free of charge for this camp. Shunsuke Aoki, an individual member, kindly provided konashi. This camp will be reported in the Unexplored Research Group #3.
 
 If the MISHOP can accumulate the know-how of development camps and hold more and more such camps, it will lead to "accelerating innovation centered on IT by supporting creative human resources from various perspectives and creating cross-industry networks," which is the purpose of MISHOP. The next meeting will be held in September. The next meeting is scheduled to be held around September.
